This is a list of the [[national park]]s in the [[Baltic states]] of [[Estonia]], [[Latvia]], and [[Lithuania]].
==Estonia== [[File:Karula RP2.JPG|thumb|alt=Landscape in Karula national park, Estonia.|[[Karula National Park]] (Estonia)]] There are 5 [[national park]]s in [[Estonia]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Estonian Nature Conservation in 2007 |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |year=2008 |publisher=Estonian Environment Information Centre |location=Tallinn |isbn=978-9985-881-56-9 |page=29 |pages= |url=http://www.keskkonnainfo.ee/publications/327_PDF.pdf}}</ref> *[[Karula National Park]] 1993 *[[Lahemaa National Park]] 1971 *[[Soomaa National Park]] 1993 *[[Vilsandi National Park]] 1993 *[[Matsalu National Park]] 2004
==Latvia== [[File:Zvartes rock.jpg|thumb|alt=Nature in Gauja National Park, Latvia.|[[Gauja National Park]] (Latvia)]] There are 4 [[national park]]s in [[Latvia]]. *[[Gauja National Park]] 1973 *[[Rāzna National Park]] 2007 *[[Ķemeri National Park]] 1997 *[[Slītere National Park]] 1999
==Lithuania== [[File:Pilkosios kopos1.jpg|thumb|alt=Sand dunes in Kuršių Nerija National Park, Lithuania|[[Kuršių Nerija National Park]] (Lithuania)]] There are 5 national parks in Lithuania. They were established in 1991 after [[Lithuania]] declared independence from the [[Soviet Union]] in 1990. [[Lithuanian SSR]] National Park established in 1974 was reorganized and renamed Aukštaitija National Park. Now they cover about 2.3 percent of Lithuania's territory.
