um FAQ|publisher=}}</ref><ref name="opossum2">[http://opossum.craton.net/faqs.htm Craton.net]</ref> * [[Owl]] * [[Panamanian night monkey]]<ref name="monk3">{{cite web|url=http://pin.primate.wisc.edu/factsheets/entry/owl_monkey|title=Primate Factsheets: Owl monkey (Aotus) Taxonomy, Morphology, & Ecology|publisher=}}</ref><ref name="monk4">{{cite web|url=http://www.iucnredlist.org/apps/redlist/details/39953/0|title=Aotus zonalis (Panamanian Night Monkey)|publisher=}}</ref> * [[Pangolin]]<ref name="pangolin">{{cite web|url=http://www.awf.org/content/wildlife/detail/pangolin |title=Pangolin |work=African Wildlife Foundation |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090417080037/http://www.awf.org/content/wildlife/detail/pangolin |archivedate=2009-04-17 |df= }}</ref> * [[Pseudis paradoxa|Paradoxical frog]]<ref name="pfrog1">{{cite web|url=http://www.wildanimalsonline.com/amphibians/paradoxicalfrog.php|title=Paradoxical frog ( Pseudis paradoxus ) - Paradoxical frog information - Paradoxical frog facts - WildAnimalsOnline.com|publisher=}}</ref><ref name="pfrog2">{{cite web|url=http://www.buzzle.com/articles/nocturnal-animals.html|title=Nocturnal Animals|publisher=}}</ref> * [[Porcupine]]<ref name="pornoc">{{cite web | url=http://www.nhm.org/site/explore-exhibits/permanent-exhibits/north-american-mammals/porcupine | title=North American porcupine&nbsp;— Erethizon dorsatum (Linnaeus, 1758) | publisher=Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County | accessdate=July 26, 2012}}</ref> * [[Phalangeriformes|Possum]]<ref name="possum">{{cite web|url=http://rainforest-australia.com/possums.htm|title=! Rainforest Possums ! Tropical Rainforest, Far North Queensland Australia|author=John Chambers|publisher=}}</ref> * ''[[Python regius]]''<ref name="python">[http://www.nadvethosp.com/includes/file.asp?file_id=67 Nad Al Shiba Veterinary Hospital]</ref> * [[Quoll]] * [[Rabbit rat]]<ref name="rabbitrat">{{cite web|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/cgi-bin/sprat/public/publicsp